abstract: Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren on Thursday declined to disavow a new super PAC that has earmarked $1 million to back her candidacy, an apparent reversal from her vigorous opposition to the outside spending groups that have become central to American politics.
snippet: Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren on Thursday declined to disavow a new super PAC that has earmarked $1 million to back her candidacy, an apparent reversal from her vigorous opposition to the outside spending groups that have become...
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren on Thursday declined to disavow a new super PAC that has earmarked $1 million to back her candidacy, an apparent reversal from her vigorous opposition to the outside spending groups that have become central to American politics.
headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Appears to Drop Opposition to Unlimited-Money Group Backing Her Campaign
headline_print_headline: Elizabeth Warren Appears to Drop Opposition to Unlimited-Money Group Backing Her Campaign

abstract: Exuberant over the candidates’ performances, he continued his tour through the West.

abstract: His aura suddenly shattered, a defiant Michael Bloomberg sent a pointed message Thursday to a political world grappling with his underwhelming presidential debate debut: He's not going away.
snippet: His aura suddenly shattered, a defiant Michael Bloomberg sent a pointed message Thursday to a political world grappling with his underwhelming presidential debate debut: He's not going away.
lead_paragraph: SALT LAKE CITY — His aura suddenly shattered, a defiant Michael Bloomberg sent a pointed message Thursday to a political world grappling with his underwhelming presidential debate debut: He's not going away.
headline_main: Wounded but Defiant, Bloomberg Promises to Keep Fighting
headline_print_headline: Wounded but Defiant, Bloomberg Promises to Keep Fighting

abstract: Dems should be talking about financialization and fraud.
snippet: Dems should be talking about financialization and fraud.
lead_paragraph: Wednesday’s Democratic debate was far more informative than previous debates. What we learned, in particular, was that as a presidential candidate, Michael Bloomberg is a great businessman — and that Elizabeth Warren remains a force to be reckoned with.

abstract: A group of Los Angeles artists were awaiting the results of the Democratic Party’s Iowa caucuses, hoping Bernie Sanders would win, when they fired off a hashtag on Twitter poking fun at Pete Buttigieg.
